WEBVTT

00:46.129 --> 00:47.289
MAN: These are perennial.

00:47.798 --> 00:49.459
That means they come back every year.

00:50.467 --> 00:52.799
You don't have to replant them
or anything, they just come back.

00:53.637 --> 00:55.969
- Every year?
- Every year. Forever.

00:57.641 --> 00:59.506
These were your
mother's favorite, peonies.

01:00.644 --> 01:02.054
She liked how fluffy they are.

01:04.982 --> 01:06.142
Pretty fluffy for a flower.

01:07.985 --> 01:09.100
Yeah. (CHUCKLES)

01:11.488 --> 01:12.773
Here. Come on.

01:13.657 --> 01:14.646
That's good, Maggie.

02:04.708 --> 02:06.790
(ENGINE REWING)

02:12.049 --> 02:14.040
(ENGINE WHIRRING)

02:33.570 --> 02:36.186
Hey! Hey!

02:37.616 --> 02:38.605
Stop it!

02:39.993 --> 02:40.982
Stop it.

02:41.995 --> 02:43.280
Trying to get yourself killed?

02:44.456 --> 02:45.741
What are you doing here?

02:46.208 --> 02:47.197
(TURNS OFF ENGINE)

02:48.085 --> 02:49.074
Get out of my way.

02:50.587 --> 02:51.997
Get out of my way!

02:52.089 --> 02:53.954
You're not allowed to do this!

02:54.257 --> 02:56.748
You don't get out of the way,
I'm gonna run you over.

02:57.010 --> 02:58.625
All right, so get out of the way.

02:59.429 --> 03:00.794
Go. (STARTS ENGINE)

03:05.310 --> 03:07.050
MAGGIE: He almost ran over me.

03:07.437 --> 03:09.177
- With a backhoe?
- Twice.

03:10.107 --> 03:12.314
- How did he get it up there?
- Who cares?

03:12.776 --> 03:13.982
Just trying to get
the facts here, Maggie.

03:14.069 --> 03:15.605
Did you see him drive it up there?

03:15.737 --> 03:17.648
He took it up the logging road.

03:18.949 --> 03:19.938
How did he look?

03:20.784 --> 03:22.024
I guess he looked pretty good

03:22.119 --> 03:23.825
for an asshole
digging a hole on my property.

03:24.287 --> 03:25.652
- He looked just fine.
- Okay.

03:25.789 --> 03:27.120
I want you to arrest him.

03:27.624 --> 03:28.739
Come on, Maggie.

03:28.834 --> 03:30.449
Don't make excuses for him.

03:30.544 --> 03:33.331
I'm not making excuses.
He's definitely a knucklehead.

03:33.547 --> 03:34.787
Yeah, he's a knucklehead,

03:34.881 --> 03:37.964
with a backhoe,
digging a huge hole in my property.

03:38.468 --> 03:41.301
Okay, let's go
and take a look at this.

04:04.703 --> 04:05.818
RAY: Man, is he good with that thing.

04:08.665 --> 04:10.326
It's kind of little for a backhoe,
isn't it?

04:17.214 --> 04:18.625
RAY: Uh-oh, look at this.

04:19.091 --> 04:20.081
Who's that?

04:21.094 --> 04:22.209
Ben's sister.

04:22.512 --> 04:24.673
God damn it, there are more of them.
He brought friends.

04:24.765 --> 04:26.721
LOGAN: Let me take care of this.
Maggie... (SIGHS)

04:27.476 --> 04:29.341
- Get off of my property.
- Ben.

04:30.061 --> 04:31.301
Ben Farmer.

04:33.648 --> 04:34.637
Ben Farmer.

04:34.733 --> 04:35.722
(ENGINE STOPS)

04:36.026 --> 04:37.015
Hey, Maggie.

04:37.486 --> 04:40.102
God damn it, Gerry.
Man, what are you doing here?

04:40.655 --> 04:42.111
Well, Ben called me.
He said the two of you were...

04:42.199 --> 04:44.440
Yeah, don't tell me about it.
I don't want to know.

04:44.534 --> 04:45.944
You two, out, out.

04:48.163 --> 04:49.573
I thought they worked this out.

04:51.500 --> 04:52.489
RAY: Well, I guess not.

04:53.001 --> 04:54.537
You, get off my land.

04:55.212 --> 04:57.203
We got a bit
of a situation here, Ben.

04:57.506 --> 04:59.792
Logan, I don't see
how this is any of your business.

04:59.883 --> 05:03.375
It's his business because you're
breaking the law, you asshole.

05:03.637 --> 05:07.050
You clearly don't
understand everything, as usual.

05:07.307 --> 05:08.342
This is my land, Logan.

05:08.433 --> 05:09.889
- Oh, for fuck's sake, it is not.
- My land.

05:10.060 --> 05:11.641
You were never
meant to have the whole place.

05:11.728 --> 05:13.309
For one thing,
you aren't keeping it up.

05:13.480 --> 05:16.062
- Her husband died, the whole place...
- You leave him out of it.

05:16.149 --> 05:19.391
Oh, oh, oh. Yeah, he robbed me,
she robbed me, both of them robbed me.

05:19.486 --> 05:20.475
- Now, it's mine.
- Bullshit.

05:20.737 --> 05:23.149
You came to that office,
to that lawyer's office,

05:23.240 --> 05:25.026
and I said, "If we give you

05:25.116 --> 05:26.481
- "a good price for that land...
- Maggie.

05:26.660 --> 05:28.901
"...you can't come back here
in 20 years."

05:29.079 --> 05:30.615
- Oh, good Christ, you fucked me.
- She is something.

05:30.705 --> 05:32.536
- Okay.
- She is so crazy.

05:32.624 --> 05:35.491
- Okay, listen.
- It might interest you to know, Logan,

05:35.585 --> 05:38.167
that I acquired this land legally,
two weeks ago.

05:38.255 --> 05:40.997
"Acquired this land."
Who did you acquire it from?

05:41.091 --> 05:42.797
- Because I didn't sell it to you.
- Oh, didn't you?

05:42.884 --> 05:44.420
- No.
- Okay, you're claiming...

05:44.761 --> 05:45.750
No, not claiming.

05:46.096 --> 05:48.428
No, I have the permits.
I have everything in the truck.

05:48.598 --> 05:49.804
That's bullshit! Bullshit!

05:49.891 --> 05:52.177
Hey, Ben. We gonna go back to work?

05:52.435 --> 05:55.427
- No, you're going home.
- Oh, round two.

05:55.730 --> 05:58.096
- Now she's gonna harass my workers?
- Ben. Ben.

05:58.191 --> 05:59.806
- I got the papers, okay.
- MAGGIE: I don't know what

05:59.901 --> 06:01.607
they told you, and I don't care,
but I'm telling you,

06:01.778 --> 06:04.770
as the owner of this property,
that you are violating my rights.

06:04.990 --> 06:08.528
And if you don't leave now,
immediately, I'm going to...

06:08.827 --> 06:11.910
You will be arrested and charged.

06:15.292 --> 06:16.953
- It's not funny, Gerry.
- GERRY: It...

06:17.335 --> 06:18.700
It is kind of funny, Maggie.

06:18.837 --> 06:20.077
No, it's not.

06:20.672 --> 06:22.708
- You look good.
- (G ROANS)

06:22.966 --> 06:24.877
LOGAN: You're gonna have to let me
take care of this, Maggie.

06:24.968 --> 06:26.128
You're not taking care of anything.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.126
There's a huge hole right there.

06:28.221 --> 06:29.711
Go on. Get in the truck.

06:30.473 --> 06:31.838
You want me to get in the truck?

06:32.058 --> 06:33.889
Yes, I want you to get in the truck.

06:34.561 --> 06:36.267
You can't tell me
to get in the truck!

06:36.354 --> 06:39.517
I am telling you to get in the truck.
Come on.

06:40.400 --> 06:41.389
Come on.

06:49.242 --> 06:50.231
She's fucked.

06:51.453 --> 06:52.989
She's out of her mind.

06:55.290 --> 07:00.125
Because I have the permit.

07:00.712 --> 07:02.452
Maggie, I'm gonna need you
to go on home.

07:02.547 --> 07:04.503
I'll call you when I have
more of a handle on this.

07:06.343 --> 07:07.332
Go on.

07:10.138 --> 07:11.548
(ENGINE STARTS)

07:27.238 --> 07:29.524
Hi, this is Maggie Kramer.

07:29.824 --> 07:31.689
I was just wondering
if you got that idiot,

07:31.785 --> 07:34.822
otherwise known as my brother,
off my property.

07:36.206 --> 07:37.946
This is a serious matter,

07:38.041 --> 07:41.533
and, frankly, I hope you arrested
that fucking son of a bitch.

08:08.863 --> 08:09.978
(CLATTERING)

08:13.243 --> 08:14.574
That was stupid.

08:16.413 --> 08:18.119
Hi, Mrs. Kramer. This is Elise.

08:18.581 --> 08:21.493
It's Maggie Kramer. She also left you
two messages on your voicemail.

08:21.584 --> 08:23.165
I am not in yet.

08:24.087 --> 08:26.203
He's not in yet, Mrs. Kramer.
Can I take a message?

08:28.591 --> 08:31.082
And I'm sure he will
as soon as he gets in.

08:37.142 --> 08:40.179
- What's that about?
- Ben Farmer, making trouble again.

08:40.270 --> 08:41.385
Who knows what he's up to?

08:42.063 --> 08:43.644
It'll take me a few days
to sort it out.

09:34.199 --> 09:36.155
Ben, you up?

09:36.326 --> 09:37.441
Yeah, I'm up.

09:37.786 --> 09:38.992
I brought you coffee.

09:43.541 --> 09:44.530
BEN: Lord.

09:46.461 --> 09:47.450
Yeah.

09:48.922 --> 09:50.002
Oh, he's, uh...

09:50.799 --> 09:53.006
He's staying out here now? Your kid?

09:54.969 --> 09:56.675
- Is that a problem?
- No.

09:59.265 --> 10:01.096
I didn't know whether you
needed me today or not.

10:01.851 --> 10:03.182
(CH UCKLING) Absolutely.

10:05.188 --> 10:07.099
You work things out with Maggie?

10:07.565 --> 10:08.554
What did I say?

10:11.444 --> 10:14.060
Look, I can't, um...

10:14.155 --> 10:17.522
I can't get in the middle of something
between you two, all right?

10:17.784 --> 10:19.991
Before, when I asked, you said... No.

10:20.120 --> 10:21.576
You said that she was fine.

10:21.663 --> 10:24.450
And yesterday,
she was clearly not fine.

10:25.708 --> 10:28.074
This is not your concern,
because I'm handling it.

10:28.378 --> 10:29.834
It is my concern.

10:33.716 --> 10:37.504
Look, I... I gotta return the backhoe

10:38.221 --> 10:39.506
if it's not a legal site.

10:41.015 --> 10:42.255
You're still pining for her,
is that it?

10:42.350 --> 10:43.339
Okay. (MUMBLES)

10:43.434 --> 10:46.096
No, please. I saw you when
she pulled up. You about fell over.

10:46.896 --> 10:50.138
- You're crazy.
- "I love you. I love you, Maggie.

10:50.358 --> 10:51.347
- "It doesn't matter...
- Oh, shut up.

10:51.442 --> 10:53.307
"...that you tossed me aside
for Tom Kramer."

10:53.570 --> 10:55.401
Oh, you asshole. You asshole.

10:57.031 --> 10:59.363
I'm the asshole. Fuck.

11:00.493 --> 11:02.074
- What's up with him?
- (SCOFFS)

11:03.163 --> 11:04.152
Who knows?

11:06.040 --> 11:08.827
Hey, listen. I can't go up
to the, uh, site with you today.

11:11.045 --> 11:14.162
Come on! No, I only have
the backhoe for one week.

11:14.257 --> 11:16.122
- I've got this parole thing.
- (SCOFFS)

11:16.217 --> 11:17.923
You know, might go to the Y,
and take a shower.

11:21.431 --> 11:22.420
Whatever.

11:47.624 --> 11:48.613
(EXHALES)

12:37.173 --> 12:39.289
(GRUNTS) God!

13:05.076 --> 13:06.065
(SIGHS)

13:34.397 --> 13:36.058
(DISTANT ENGINE STARTING)

13:48.036 --> 13:49.025
(ENGINE STOPS)

14:07.013 --> 14:08.219
What's this?

14:27.367 --> 14:29.449
You get off my land now.

14:31.037 --> 14:32.493
Put that down.

14:33.039 --> 14:36.247
You get off my land right now,
or I'm gonna shoot you.

14:37.293 --> 14:41.707
I said put that thing down
before you hurt somebody.

14:42.131 --> 14:43.291
Crazy bitch.

14:44.967 --> 14:45.956
Ow!

14:46.052 --> 14:47.041
(GROANING)

14:51.432 --> 14:52.797
You shot me.

14:53.184 --> 14:54.640
I said I was going to.

14:54.936 --> 14:57.769
You're not allowed
to just shoot people.

14:57.980 --> 15:00.517
You're not allowed to do
a lot of the things that you do,

15:00.608 --> 15:02.269
- but you do them anyway.
- It hurts.

15:02.360 --> 15:03.349
Stomping on my garden.

15:03.694 --> 15:06.185
I can't believe you did that.
I can't believe you.

15:06.447 --> 15:07.436
(PANTING)

15:08.324 --> 15:10.940
I'm calling the cops. (CHUCKLES)

15:11.035 --> 15:12.491
Oh, good luck with that.

15:12.829 --> 15:16.071
I called them.
They didn't do a fucking thing.

15:16.499 --> 15:18.410
And you know what?
They don't like you.

15:18.668 --> 15:21.831
You know what that useless sheriff
calls you behind your back?

15:22.004 --> 15:23.460
He calls you a knucklehead.

15:24.006 --> 15:26.668
No, I'm telling you, you are fucked.

15:26.843 --> 15:28.879
You are really fucked this time.

15:30.430 --> 15:33.092
I'm standing here with a gun,
and you're telling me stuff?

15:33.182 --> 15:34.171
I'm telling you...

15:36.018 --> 15:38.009
Asking you, asking.

15:38.646 --> 15:40.261
Don't shoot me again, okay.
Don't kill me.

15:41.315 --> 15:42.350
That's better.

15:43.860 --> 15:44.849
God damn.

15:47.363 --> 15:48.523
Aren't you gonna help me?

15:58.416 --> 15:59.656
(MOANING)

16:17.185 --> 16:20.268
Hey! I got somebody here
who needs some attention.

16:22.648 --> 16:24.388
There was an accident with a shotgun.

16:25.318 --> 16:26.353
(GROANS)

16:26.652 --> 16:28.392
You... You put him
in the back of the truck?

16:28.738 --> 16:29.727
He's all right.

16:29.864 --> 16:31.479
I'm not all right. She shot me.

16:33.409 --> 16:35.491
- BEN: (GROANS) No...
- Can I get some help over here?

16:35.578 --> 16:37.318
I can walk here, I can walk.

16:37.455 --> 16:38.945
- Clear that way, please.
- I can walk.

16:39.373 --> 16:41.785
It's that one! She shot me!

16:42.418 --> 16:44.079
With a gun. (GROANING)

16:45.796 --> 16:47.582
What a baby. (SCOFFS)

16:56.015 --> 16:57.221
Your lawyer's here.

16:58.100 --> 16:59.306
I didn't call him.

16:59.435 --> 17:01.847
I did. You can't sit here all day.

17:02.897 --> 17:04.603
I didn't ask you to arrest me.

17:07.108 --> 17:08.565
Hey, you gonna let me out?

17:09.111 --> 17:10.521
Are you gonna shoot anybody else?

17:11.071 --> 17:12.060
Why would I?

17:13.281 --> 17:14.613
(SIGHING) Oh, boy.

17:26.878 --> 17:28.540
My car is right there, yeah.

17:29.382 --> 17:32.044
So Logan said Ben
had some crazy story.

17:32.134 --> 17:35.001
He's always got some crazy story.
What's new?

17:35.513 --> 17:38.550
You sold him back his half?

17:38.641 --> 17:40.427
He didn't have half of the land.

17:40.810 --> 17:43.222
Tom and I paid for that land upfront.

17:43.396 --> 17:45.136
Ben was only interested in the money.

17:45.231 --> 17:46.346
He needed the money.

17:47.108 --> 17:49.099
Stop. Whose side are you on, anyway?

17:49.235 --> 17:51.317
I'm not... I'm not taking sides.

17:51.487 --> 17:53.569
You're my lawyer.
You're supposed to take sides.

17:53.656 --> 17:54.862
You're supposed to take my side.

17:54.991 --> 17:58.074
I just... Mmm, I just wondered
if you knew why he would say that.

17:58.327 --> 18:01.364
'Cause he's a fucking lunatic,
that's why.

18:01.872 --> 18:02.861
Okay.

18:10.673 --> 18:12.709
Listen, I shot my brother.

18:12.925 --> 18:14.665
It was about time somebody did it.

18:14.844 --> 18:17.927
Everybody in this town has wanted
to shoot him at one point or another.

18:18.014 --> 18:19.629
There's no question about that.

18:19.974 --> 18:22.215
They should give me a fucking prize.

18:34.322 --> 18:36.654
DAD: Ben. Come on, Benny.

18:48.210 --> 18:51.543
So, soon as I light it, run.

18:51.881 --> 18:52.870
(MATCH STRIKING)

18:56.218 --> 18:57.207
I'm afraid.

18:57.803 --> 18:58.792
I'm not.

18:59.805 --> 19:01.261
DAD: Go. Go.

19:10.024 --> 19:11.013
(INAUDIBLE)

19:42.014 --> 19:43.094
Hey.

19:43.349 --> 19:45.556
Yeah, hey. I'm glad you called.

19:46.894 --> 19:47.883
You okay?

19:48.145 --> 19:51.137
Yeah, I'm fine.
I just need a ride, that's all.

19:51.607 --> 19:54.314
Yeah. I was over at Williams'
this morning,

19:55.277 --> 19:56.767
and I heard that you got arrested.

19:57.029 --> 19:58.610
It's totally ridiculous.

19:59.448 --> 20:00.938
Well, I heard that you shot Ben.

20:01.784 --> 20:03.194
He was invading my property,

20:03.285 --> 20:05.992
and, yes, I did shoot him,
and I should've shot him worse.

20:06.163 --> 20:09.405
And what you were doing hanging out
with him, I don't even want to know.

20:09.500 --> 20:13.209
All right, look. He told me that
he worked this out with you, okay.

20:13.295 --> 20:15.752
And Tom's been gone a year now,
so I thought maybe you had decided...

20:15.840 --> 20:18.377
No, I decided nothing,
and you thought wrong.

20:25.307 --> 20:26.296
(SIGHS)

20:32.982 --> 20:36.145
- Thanks for the ride. Appreciate it.
- You're welcome.

21:05.514 --> 21:06.549
He's not here anymore.

21:09.685 --> 21:10.845
Well, where did he go?

21:12.271 --> 21:13.852
It says he signed himself out.

21:15.524 --> 21:16.604
But he's not dead?

21:16.692 --> 21:18.182
Yeah, it says he walked out
on his own steam.

21:18.277 --> 21:19.392
After that, I don't know.

21:21.071 --> 21:22.607
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

21:34.502 --> 21:35.912
Whoo! Yeah.

21:38.214 --> 21:40.375
Maybe you shouldn't be just staying
out here in the trailer.

21:41.175 --> 21:42.460
It's my land.

21:43.093 --> 21:45.755
It's Maggie's land, Ben.
Isn't that the problem?

21:47.431 --> 21:48.796
She's in big trouble.

21:49.433 --> 21:52.140
My point being is maybe you
should stay a few days with Gerry.

21:52.228 --> 21:54.184
- Huh?
- He's got central heating.

21:55.940 --> 21:56.975
I got heating.

21:57.399 --> 21:58.684
That propane tank's so old,

21:58.943 --> 22:00.558
it's gonna explode
the next time you even look at it.

22:04.281 --> 22:05.487
God damn it.

22:10.079 --> 22:11.068
(BEN PANTING)

22:11.247 --> 22:12.236
You okay?

22:16.585 --> 22:17.574
(GRUNTS)

22:20.256 --> 22:21.416
Yeah, I'm okay.

22:30.850 --> 22:32.260
You want to smoke some weed?

22:34.520 --> 22:35.509
Yeah.

22:40.526 --> 22:41.515
(GRUNTS)

22:59.461 --> 23:01.122
RAY: Hey, Gerry.
CU RT: What's cooking, Gerry?

23:01.213 --> 23:03.579
- Hey.
- RAY: Yeah, he's in there.

23:04.633 --> 23:06.373
- BEN: Yeah.
- Yeah, it's me.

23:07.011 --> 23:08.000
BEN: Oh.

23:14.143 --> 23:15.132
Good.

23:15.603 --> 23:16.592
Yeah.

23:17.104 --> 23:18.310
Heard you got shot.

23:19.148 --> 23:21.059
- Okay?
- It's nothing.

23:23.235 --> 23:24.520
Told you you should've waited.

23:25.154 --> 23:26.485
I had the backhoe.

23:26.780 --> 23:28.771
Talk to him, he's all,
"You only have it for one week."

23:28.866 --> 23:30.822
- GERRY: That's all I could get it for.
- Yeah, whatever.

23:31.952 --> 23:33.032
Maggie shot you.

23:34.163 --> 23:35.243
She really did.

23:35.664 --> 23:37.279
She's a piece of work.

23:37.583 --> 23:40.996
You all know that she stole
that land from me.

23:41.170 --> 23:43.377
My father left me half the property.

23:43.547 --> 23:46.505
At the first Sign of trouble
that I get into,

23:46.592 --> 23:48.128
it doesn't matter what it was.

23:49.011 --> 23:53.254
She doesn't say, "Hey, let's give Ben
a little time to work this out.

23:54.016 --> 23:56.553
"He's in trouble. He's my brother.

23:56.977 --> 23:58.342
"He deserves kindness."

24:00.189 --> 24:03.727
That asshole that she got married to,
I mean, he was in on it, too.

24:04.276 --> 24:07.143
I mean, the two of them tried
to rob me of my inheritance.

24:08.030 --> 24:09.861
God damn, no, no.

24:09.949 --> 24:15.069
I mean, the time has finally come
for me to say, "No, no.

24:15.162 --> 24:16.151
(CURT COUGHING)

24:18.290 --> 24:19.279
"NO."

24:21.251 --> 24:22.582
- (BEN GROANS)
- Wow.

24:23.462 --> 24:25.498
She really got you.

24:25.673 --> 24:27.538
That's what I'm saying. Jeez!

24:27.716 --> 24:30.549
I told my wife
Ben's sister tried to kill him.

24:30.678 --> 24:32.885
She says, "About time somebody did."
(LAUGHING)

24:34.723 --> 24:35.803
She said that?

24:36.350 --> 24:39.308
Yeah. And then the kids started up...

24:39.395 --> 24:40.680
- (lMITATES GUNSHOTS)
- (CHUCKLES)

24:42.022 --> 24:43.728
Yeah, the wife didn't like that.

24:44.066 --> 24:46.307
But they got to learn sometime,
those kids.

24:46.402 --> 24:48.063
- (CURT LAUGHING)
- RAY: You know women.

24:48.696 --> 24:49.981
They don't like shooting.

24:50.531 --> 24:53.898
Well, maybe Maggie, I guess, but...

24:54.910 --> 24:56.275
(GERRY COUGHING)

24:56.912 --> 24:58.743
Lord, lwish I'd been there
to see that.

24:59.248 --> 25:01.409
- Me, too.
- Easy now. Hey, hey.

25:01.500 --> 25:04.082
Yeah, well, I mean,
it would've been something.

25:06.171 --> 25:09.379
Hey, can you give me a little of that?

25:09.675 --> 25:10.664
You just came from the hospital.

25:10.759 --> 25:12.169
I thought they'd give you
some Vicodin

25:12.261 --> 25:14.092
- or some Percocet or something.
- Give me.

25:14.471 --> 25:18.089
No, they told me if I checked
myself out, I was on my own.

25:19.143 --> 25:21.134
- (lMITATES FANFARE)
- (LAUGHING)

25:22.688 --> 25:24.553
Let me just write that.

25:25.858 --> 25:28.645
Sheriff, Mrs. Kramer's
here to see you.

25:30.112 --> 25:32.398
Maggie, how you doing today?
Shoot anybody?

25:33.240 --> 25:35.447
There hasn't really
been a need to, yet.

25:35.743 --> 25:37.233
(CHUCKLES) How can I help you?

25:38.370 --> 25:40.611
I want you to drop
those charges against me.

25:41.623 --> 25:42.863
That's a matter for the courts.

25:42.958 --> 25:44.368
I barely even winged Ben.

25:44.460 --> 25:46.576
He up and walked out
of the hospital this morning.

25:46.962 --> 25:49.203
You can explain that to your lawyer.

25:50.007 --> 25:52.123
You drop your charges,
and I'll drop mine.

25:54.595 --> 25:55.584
Your charges?

25:56.055 --> 25:58.592
I am bringing charges
of criminal trespass

25:58.682 --> 26:01.048
and destruction of property
against my brother.

26:01.143 --> 26:02.508
(SIGHS)

26:04.104 --> 26:05.844
Shouldn't she be writing this down?

26:07.316 --> 26:09.181
Elise, if Maggie
wants to bring charges,

26:09.276 --> 26:10.516
what does she need to do?

26:11.737 --> 26:13.147
She needs to talk to her lawyer.

26:14.073 --> 26:16.655
Are you kidding?
What was I supposed to do?

26:16.784 --> 26:18.570
He was digging a huge hole
on my property.

26:18.660 --> 26:19.649
You didn't do a thing.

26:20.204 --> 26:22.069
Maggie, he had the permits.

26:22.331 --> 26:23.491
And how did he get them?

26:23.624 --> 26:25.660
Did you look into that? No.

26:27.086 --> 26:28.496
Some sheriff.

26:29.004 --> 26:30.494
You should arrest yourself.

26:57.533 --> 26:58.522
Hey, Rachel.

26:59.201 --> 27:01.783
Sheriff, what can I do for you?

27:01.870 --> 27:03.610
I'm here to look at some land grants.

27:03.872 --> 27:05.908
Okay. Which ones?

27:05.999 --> 27:08.411
Well, just one, actually.
The Farmer property.

27:11.088 --> 27:12.077
Hmm.

27:14.216 --> 27:15.672
(SIGHING) I don't...

27:16.301 --> 27:18.383
That's not how things
are filed around here.

27:18.762 --> 27:21.970
You don't happen to remember
a lot number?

27:22.391 --> 27:23.380
A lot number?

27:24.017 --> 27:26.383
Things are filed...
They're not filed according to names.

27:27.563 --> 27:28.848
You don't remember the lot number?

27:29.314 --> 27:30.303
Well, you know where it is.

27:30.399 --> 27:31.479
It's right up there
at the end of the hollow.

27:32.568 --> 27:34.684
Mmm, which one is it?

27:35.404 --> 27:37.565
Look, I've got these building permits

27:37.656 --> 27:41.569
that you approved of for Ben Farmer
just this week.

27:43.203 --> 27:44.238
You know what lot it is.

27:47.666 --> 27:50.908
Oh. That's the property
you're talking about. Sure.

27:51.962 --> 27:52.951
Are you okay?

27:53.046 --> 27:54.877
Yeah, I just never did it
this way before.

28:08.270 --> 28:09.305
Could you excuse me for a second?

28:09.396 --> 28:11.102
I just remembered
I have to make a phone call.

28:34.796 --> 28:35.785
Have a seat.

28:41.887 --> 28:43.468
(CHUCKLES)

28:43.722 --> 28:45.303
You're just trying to get me
to calm down,

28:45.390 --> 28:47.096
and the problem with that
is that you don't actually let me,

28:47.184 --> 28:48.890
like, talk through
what I'm actually feeling.

28:48.977 --> 28:51.343
And more important than that, like,
it just upsets me even more,

28:51.438 --> 28:53.099
because you're not hearing
what actually happened today.

28:53.357 --> 28:54.813
And what actually happened,
like, the facts,

28:54.900 --> 28:56.891
are that the Sheriff came
into my place of work,

28:57.027 --> 28:59.393
and was asking for documents
that I didn't want to give him.

28:59.488 --> 29:01.069
He was being
really, really nice about it,

29:01.156 --> 29:03.863
like, the kind of nice that's, like,
you know that you're screwed.

29:04.159 --> 29:06.650
- What did he say?
- He made me show him everything.

29:06.828 --> 29:08.739
Everything about that
piece of land that you...

29:08.830 --> 29:10.320
"Everything." What do you mean
by "everything"?

29:10.666 --> 29:12.372
You told me that this was legal.

29:12.960 --> 29:13.949
You need any help?

29:14.544 --> 29:15.533
No, we don't.

29:17.839 --> 29:19.875
- We're good.
- He meant a drink.

29:21.551 --> 29:23.337
I'll have a white wine
Spritzer, please.

29:24.429 --> 29:25.965
I'll have a beer,
whatever you got on tap.

29:26.056 --> 29:27.842
Thank you very much. Thank you.

29:34.106 --> 29:35.892
Everything that we're doing is legal.

29:36.024 --> 29:37.685
Oh, my God. I gave you those permits

29:37.776 --> 29:39.312
because you told me
you had logging rights.

29:39.528 --> 29:40.517
- And...
- We do.

29:40.612 --> 29:42.603
No, and you also told me that Ben
was gonna buy the land back

29:42.698 --> 29:44.484
because she was behind on her taxes.

29:44.866 --> 29:46.276
- You told me that.
- Yes.

29:46.368 --> 29:48.324
CURT: She's like $50,000 behind.

29:48.412 --> 29:49.572
RACHEL: Why couldn't you just wait?

29:49.830 --> 29:51.070
Gerry had the backhoe.

29:51.498 --> 29:52.487
(RACHEL SIGHS)

29:53.041 --> 29:56.704
Do you... Do you understand that
without the underlying documents,

29:56.795 --> 29:59.036
the permits are illegal? They are.

30:00.215 --> 30:01.876
And why did you
show them to the Sheriff?

30:01.967 --> 30:03.878
Hey, look, did he say
you're under arrest?

30:05.721 --> 30:07.586
Did he say you're going to jail?

30:07.681 --> 30:09.637
Mmm... No.

30:10.225 --> 30:11.931
Did he say you're going to hell?

30:13.270 --> 30:17.263
Curt, you told me that
I was not gonna get in trouble.

30:18.150 --> 30:19.356
You're not in trouble.

30:22.738 --> 30:23.773
You promise?

30:31.747 --> 30:32.953
I'm hungry.

30:34.291 --> 30:35.781
(BEN STRAINING)

30:36.585 --> 30:40.498
Well, let's see.
I've got some cheese and crackers,

30:40.672 --> 30:43.755
some summer sausage,
there's tomatoes, I think.

30:44.343 --> 30:48.006
Uh, there's peaches
I got at the farm stand,

30:48.513 --> 30:50.549
there's some corn somewhere,

30:51.058 --> 30:54.550
hamburger in the fridge
and noodles in the closet.

30:55.312 --> 30:56.301
Oh.

31:04.196 --> 31:05.686
You're shitting me, aren't you?

31:06.281 --> 31:07.817
(BEN AND RAY CHUCKLE)

31:08.575 --> 31:10.440
I think there's
some peanuts somewhere.

31:10.619 --> 31:12.325
- (SIGHS)
- (RAY CHUCKLING)

31:18.627 --> 31:20.709
Hey, Curt, what took you so long?

31:20.921 --> 31:22.786
We're starving up here.
You bring any food?

31:23.465 --> 31:24.454
(GROANS)

31:25.300 --> 31:26.665
Some shit going on.

31:27.594 --> 31:28.925
Yeah, what kind of shit?

31:29.012 --> 31:30.627
Some "we got a problem" shit.

31:31.973 --> 31:33.634
The Sheriff's gonna make trouble.

31:33.725 --> 31:35.306
The Sheriff, the short guy?

31:35.394 --> 31:36.383
Yeah.

31:36.561 --> 31:37.801
The Sheriff's stirring up shit.

31:39.064 --> 31:40.850
Hey, tell me later.

31:47.322 --> 31:48.311
Gerry.

31:51.952 --> 31:52.987
Where are the peanuts?

31:55.622 --> 31:56.657
Peanuts?

32:00.168 --> 32:01.999
- BEN: I'll get them.
- Oh, no. In the...

32:02.170 --> 32:06.334
No, peanuts and the summer sausage.

32:07.717 --> 32:10.504
- BEN: Don't forget the noodles.
- (RAY LAUGHING)

32:11.221 --> 32:13.382
BEN: So, you told the Sheriff.

32:13.473 --> 32:15.338
I didn't tell him anything.

32:15.892 --> 32:17.598
Look, just so you know,

32:18.437 --> 32:19.847
you're not in trouble.

32:20.856 --> 32:23.598
She's the one
who's in trouble, all right?

32:23.692 --> 32:24.727
She shot me.

32:25.485 --> 32:28.227
(CHUCKLES) There's no
getting around that, right.

32:28.947 --> 32:29.936
I'm wounded.

32:31.283 --> 32:33.023
She's in big fucking trouble.

32:33.869 --> 32:36.781
And the boom
is coming down on my sister.

32:37.456 --> 32:39.196
Okay. Yes.

32:39.624 --> 32:41.285
But there are other people

32:41.376 --> 32:43.207
looking into this situation
right now.

32:43.753 --> 32:45.163
But this is what I'm saying.

32:45.464 --> 32:48.251
You don't have
to worry about it, right.

32:48.383 --> 32:52.592
You don't have to talk
about it with anybody, all right.

32:52.721 --> 32:54.461
- Well...
- This is all on her.

32:54.681 --> 32:55.796
It's... (LAUGHING)

32:55.891 --> 32:58.473
She has been caught in a web
of her own making.

32:58.560 --> 32:59.891
It took years.

33:00.562 --> 33:04.555
It took time, a lot of years
of planning and execution.

33:04.900 --> 33:10.566
It's only her malfeasance
and ingratitude and disloyalty

33:11.406 --> 33:13.897
that have brought her to this point.

33:14.326 --> 33:17.864
And it is nothing that we did.

33:18.622 --> 33:22.410
It's just the poisonous defects
of her own disappointing character.

33:24.753 --> 33:26.084
(DOOR OPENING)

33:31.718 --> 33:33.003
MAGGIE: Hey, Ben.

33:34.513 --> 33:35.502
Maggie.

33:36.765 --> 33:38.346
Didn't bring your shotgun, I see.

33:38.892 --> 33:40.257
You want, I can go get it.

33:40.769 --> 33:42.134
That won't be necessary.

33:42.938 --> 33:44.474
We were just on our way out.

33:46.608 --> 33:49.600
Can I thank you very much
for your help?

33:51.112 --> 33:52.227
We'll be in touch.

34:46.333 --> 34:47.665
What were you telling them?

34:48.795 --> 34:49.784
What?

34:50.088 --> 34:51.998
Did you not understand my question?

34:54.217 --> 34:55.206
I don't...

34:55.885 --> 34:57.341
I don't even know who you are.

34:57.846 --> 34:59.552
No, you don't know who I am at all.

35:00.015 --> 35:02.051
And you're letting those criminals
steal my house.

35:03.184 --> 35:04.469
Mrs. Kramer,

35:05.353 --> 35:08.220
you are very behind on your taxes.

35:08.315 --> 35:09.521
What's that to you?

35:09.816 --> 35:10.805
It is a fact.

35:11.109 --> 35:14.397
And if you lose your land,
it is not my doing.

35:15.614 --> 35:17.605
You're letting them turn you
into the kind of person

35:17.699 --> 35:21.362
who can destroy another person's life
without even thinking twice about it.

35:23.121 --> 35:24.110
I don't...

35:25.165 --> 35:27.497
- My boyfriend says...
- Your boyfriend?

35:30.712 --> 35:32.327
Dream bigger, would you?

35:33.214 --> 35:34.829
If you can't dream bigger now,

35:34.924 --> 35:37.006
you think it's ever
gonna get any better?

35:39.179 --> 35:40.385
You're crazy.

35:41.765 --> 35:42.754
Yeah.

35:43.558 --> 35:46.049
Makes you feel better
when you tell yourself that.

35:46.978 --> 35:48.093
But guess what.

35:49.731 --> 35:52.097
You're not the first person
who's tried it on me.

35:55.070 --> 35:56.310
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

36:14.589 --> 36:15.578
(SIGHS)

36:27.268 --> 36:28.348
(STARTS ENGINE)

37:24.242 --> 37:25.857
DAD: Hang on. Hang on.

37:27.537 --> 37:28.993
It's really deep.

37:29.164 --> 37:30.495
It's super-duper deep.

37:32.250 --> 37:34.036
DAD: on. Come on, bud.

37:58.067 --> 37:59.523
Ben, Ben.

38:00.904 --> 38:02.019
Go, go.

38:03.072 --> 38:04.187
Come on, Gerry.

38:26.721 --> 38:28.427
(CAR APPROACHING)

38:44.572 --> 38:45.561
Hi.

38:46.908 --> 38:47.897
Hello.

38:48.076 --> 38:49.236
Is Curt around?

38:50.870 --> 38:52.235
Do you see him anywhere?

38:52.747 --> 38:53.953
(RACHEL SCOFFS)

39:10.765 --> 39:12.926
You know, you don't
actually own that land yet.

39:15.603 --> 39:18.094
That's my land.
My father left me that land.

39:20.692 --> 39:22.933
And then you sold it
to your Sister and her husband.

39:23.027 --> 39:24.233
I read the records.

39:24.362 --> 39:26.102
They stole it, you mean.

39:27.574 --> 39:29.360
You sold it to them.

39:29.576 --> 39:31.942
It's a manner of speech.
Don't you understand anything?

39:32.620 --> 39:33.826
I mean, yeah,

39:34.622 --> 39:36.704
I signed some papers,
and they gave me some money,

39:36.791 --> 39:41.125
but it wasn't anywhere near enough.
That's what "They stole it" means.

39:43.464 --> 39:45.420
I don't think it means that.

39:46.801 --> 39:48.507
Did I invite you here?

39:48.636 --> 39:49.876
I'm waiting for Curt.

39:52.140 --> 39:53.129
Is he coming back?

39:56.561 --> 39:58.142
He's doing some business.

40:03.109 --> 40:04.098
Hey.

40:05.153 --> 40:08.145
You know that kid that makes coffee
at Gypsy Donuts?

40:10.325 --> 40:11.781
No, I don't think I know him.

40:12.827 --> 40:14.363
He's got crazy hair.

40:15.622 --> 40:16.611
Blue.

40:17.832 --> 40:20.665
I don't know anyone at Gypsy Donuts.

40:20.752 --> 40:23.164
Well, you don't have
to know him personally.

40:23.296 --> 40:26.333
I don't go into Gypsy Donuts,
so I don't think I know him.

40:27.050 --> 40:29.132
Well, he's got a great pot connection.

40:31.095 --> 40:32.426
Curt can meet you there.

40:34.057 --> 40:36.173
CU RT: Maggie's gonna default
on her taxes again.

40:36.267 --> 40:38.633
When she does, the state's gonna
auction that property off.

40:38.728 --> 40:40.719
When they do,
whoever holds the logging rights

40:40.813 --> 40:42.349
gets to be first in line to buy it.

40:43.107 --> 40:44.096
Hmm.

40:44.359 --> 40:46.645
So, what I need from you

40:47.612 --> 40:48.818
is those logging rights.

40:49.072 --> 40:51.188
Well, I need $5,000.

40:53.493 --> 40:54.733
Let me borrow them for one week.

40:59.832 --> 41:00.947
- Shit.
- What?

41:01.626 --> 41:02.615
Maggie's here.

41:03.711 --> 41:05.918
All right, just go. Hustle, man.

41:06.923 --> 41:07.912
Be quiet.

41:09.467 --> 41:10.707
"Be quiet," man. I'm sure... Shut up.

41:11.010 --> 41:12.625
You're making all the noise
telling me to be quiet.

41:12.720 --> 41:13.709
Yeah.

41:14.389 --> 41:16.220
Hey, Maggie, how you doing?

41:16.641 --> 41:19.474
- I'm okay.
- Good. You look good.

41:20.269 --> 41:23.887
You looking to let go of more
of those logging rights?

41:24.190 --> 41:25.475
- No.
- No?

41:25.566 --> 41:26.726
What I was wondering is,

41:26.818 --> 41:30.561
can I have a look at those leases
I already sold to you?

41:30.780 --> 41:31.940
What do you
want to look at those for?

41:32.031 --> 41:34.738
I want to see how much I owe.
Might buy them back.

41:34.867 --> 41:35.982
Your people aren't using them,

41:36.077 --> 41:38.534
and you never do any logging up there.

41:38.830 --> 41:39.819
I can't.

41:42.000 --> 41:42.989
Why not?

41:45.586 --> 41:46.575
Because...

41:49.090 --> 41:50.250
Oh, for heaven's sake.

41:50.508 --> 41:53.545
Wait, you can't go in there.
Now, this is private property.

41:53.636 --> 41:55.046
- So what?
- Maggie, come on now.

41:55.138 --> 41:56.423
I'm gonna call the police now.

41:56.514 --> 41:59.756
Oh, you do that. I hope it works
better for you than it worked for me.

41:59.851 --> 42:01.011
(RAY SIGHS)

42:05.189 --> 42:06.178
What's going on here?

42:06.274 --> 42:09.107
Nothing's going on.
Look, you're trespassing, okay?

42:09.193 --> 42:11.775
And if you want to see the files,
you're gonna need a warrant.

42:12.947 --> 42:14.983
- A warrant?
- You know what I mean.

42:15.074 --> 42:17.861
Just call and make an appointment.
Bring your lawyer with you.

42:17.952 --> 42:20.159
You can't just go
barging in to private property.

42:20.246 --> 42:21.611
That's not what people do.

42:22.081 --> 42:23.070
Go!

42:26.711 --> 42:27.791
Hmm.

42:37.972 --> 42:40.384
Here you go. Good to see you again.
Can I help you?

42:42.143 --> 42:43.132
Oh.

42:43.352 --> 42:44.341
L, uh...

42:47.940 --> 42:48.975
(WHISPERS) Are you Jimmy?

42:49.317 --> 42:51.433
Sorry, no. His shift doesn't start
for another 20 minutes.

42:51.527 --> 42:52.516
Is there anything I can do for you?

42:53.863 --> 42:54.852
No, I'll come back.

42:55.740 --> 42:56.946
Should I tell him
that you stopped by?

42:57.241 --> 42:59.197
No, no. No, that's okay.

42:59.660 --> 43:01.992
Oh, you're here to score
some weed, aren't you?

43:02.872 --> 43:04.988
ELISE: Hey, Rachel.
LOGAN: Rachel.

43:06.501 --> 43:07.490
Whoa!

43:08.169 --> 43:09.500
Hi, Elise.

43:10.630 --> 43:12.586
- Hello.
- Getting a cup of coffee?

43:12.757 --> 43:14.964
No. Yes. Yes.

43:15.301 --> 43:17.166
Except my

43:17.970 --> 43:18.959
wallet...

43:20.098 --> 43:22.009
I think I left it...

43:28.106 --> 43:30.893
Hey, hey.
What are you running away for?

43:31.943 --> 43:33.023
I'm not running away.

43:33.277 --> 43:34.266
You're pretty speedy.

43:35.446 --> 43:36.435
So?

43:36.864 --> 43:38.104
You didn't get your coffee, did you?

43:38.199 --> 43:39.530
I don't really need coffee.

43:39.992 --> 43:41.232
No one needs coffee.

43:41.536 --> 43:43.117
It's not really
all that good for you.

43:43.204 --> 43:45.240
That's exactly
what I was gonna say.

43:45.331 --> 43:46.537
It's not that good for you,

43:46.624 --> 43:50.037
so it's not like I should just
have coffee whenever I feel like it.

43:50.294 --> 43:51.875
Well, not whenever you feel like it.

43:52.213 --> 43:54.078
- No.
- But it's delicious.

43:55.550 --> 43:57.040
I think it's delicious.

43:58.136 --> 44:01.674
Oh, no. No, no, no.
You could get tea, like herbal tea.

44:02.890 --> 44:04.426
I don't want tea.

44:04.600 --> 44:06.056
A glass of water?

44:06.727 --> 44:09.309
Hey. Do you want a bacon donut?

44:09.397 --> 44:11.934
No, I don't...
No, just a coffee, Elise.

44:12.859 --> 44:13.894
I got to go.

44:13.985 --> 44:15.816
Well, maybe tomorrow we could...

44:18.322 --> 44:20.563
I tried to do it, Curt,
but the Sheriff is here...

44:25.079 --> 44:27.365
CU RT: It's all right.
I got it from here.

44:27.456 --> 44:28.445
Wow.

44:28.916 --> 44:30.577
Look at his arms.

44:33.713 --> 44:36.329
Honestly, I don't really know
how this is gonna work.

44:36.424 --> 44:37.914
What are you talking about?

44:38.342 --> 44:39.752
You're gonna be great.

44:40.761 --> 44:41.750
Rachel.

44:42.430 --> 44:43.636
Mrs. Farr.

44:44.015 --> 44:45.130
How are you doing, honey?

44:45.266 --> 44:48.008
Good, good. I just came to say hello.

44:49.270 --> 44:50.259
And to

44:51.314 --> 44:52.554
do some banking.

44:54.734 --> 44:57.146
So, let me hear
about what kind of banking

44:57.236 --> 44:59.022
you think you might want to do today.

44:59.447 --> 45:02.109
Well, I need... I guess I need a loan.

45:02.450 --> 45:03.439
What kind of loan, honey?

45:03.868 --> 45:04.857
Well, it's for...

45:05.953 --> 45:08.035
It's for my mom, actually.

45:08.456 --> 45:09.445
Is she okay?

45:09.582 --> 45:11.664
Yeah, she's just struggling
a little bit,

45:11.751 --> 45:14.914
and I'd love to help her out
any way that I could.

45:15.046 --> 45:17.628
You know, pay her back for college.

45:18.132 --> 45:20.498
I was thinking maybe
$10,000 or something.

45:22.136 --> 45:25.128
Well, I can get the paperwork
going on that, sure,

45:25.223 --> 45:29.136
but, honey, I can't imagine
what you have to use as collateral.

45:29.810 --> 45:30.799
Oh.

45:33.731 --> 45:36.143
Well, I have this.

45:40.363 --> 45:42.604
- Logging rights?
- Mmm-hmm.

45:44.242 --> 45:46.858
GERRY: So, Ben, you're gonna do
some logging now.

45:47.954 --> 45:50.366
Yeah. You have a problem with that?

45:51.040 --> 45:53.998
No, no, I think it's a good idea.

45:54.710 --> 45:58.373
Good. And we're cool, right?

45:58.798 --> 46:01.710
We're always cool, Ben. You just
got to pay for what you're buying.

46:01.801 --> 46:04.338
Sending that kid to steal
the papenNork, that's not right.

46:05.221 --> 46:08.429
He didn't send me. I didn't steal it.
I borrowed it.

46:08.766 --> 46:14.181
So, you used the logging rights
to borrow the money

46:14.855 --> 46:16.015
to buy them.

46:16.732 --> 46:19.018
No, actually, no,
they didn't go for that,

46:19.110 --> 46:21.066
so we used my car as collateral.

46:21.445 --> 46:23.356
Mrs. Farr knows my mom from way back

46:23.489 --> 46:26.071
and that seemed
to make the most sense.

46:27.618 --> 46:29.028
You put your car up?

46:31.706 --> 46:33.571
CURT: What can I say?
My woman loves me.

46:33.916 --> 46:35.122
She's incredible.

46:39.839 --> 46:41.295
(COUGHING)

46:50.641 --> 46:51.756
YOUNG MAGGIE: Look at the horse.

46:51.851 --> 46:53.716
YOUNG BEN: Wow, man,
that pretty horse...

46:56.439 --> 46:57.849
I like their garden.

46:58.024 --> 47:00.106
Yeah, they look pretty good.
Look at that.

47:00.401 --> 47:01.982
- It's good.
- Little stream there.

47:02.069 --> 47:03.559
Mmm-hmm. That's nice.

47:03.904 --> 47:04.893
Look at her.

47:05.031 --> 47:06.362
Hey, they look like the, urn...

47:06.449 --> 47:10.237
Those look like the flowers
Dad was talking about, you know.

47:10.328 --> 47:11.659
Oh, yeah, the fluffy ones.

47:11.746 --> 47:13.486
Yeah, the fluffy ones.
I forgot what they were called.

47:13.581 --> 47:15.117
- Look at the horse.
- Wow.

47:15.374 --> 47:17.490
Look, there's Snow White, I think.

47:17.585 --> 47:18.825
Maybe that could be Rose Red.

47:18.919 --> 47:20.159
YOUNG MAGGIE: Mmm.

47:20.254 --> 47:21.243
Yeah.

47:21.339 --> 47:22.499
Look at, like, the woods behind...

47:22.590 --> 47:24.080
Oh, yeah, that... Uh-huh.

47:24.800 --> 47:27.633
YOUNG BEN: I mean, the forest looks
a tiny bit creepy.

47:27.720 --> 47:29.881
- (CHUCKLES)
- You know, one of those...

47:29.972 --> 47:31.963
- (MIMICS CHOKING)
- YOUNG MAGGIE: Yeah.

47:32.058 --> 47:33.423
(YOUNG BEN CHUCKLES)

47:53.829 --> 47:55.945
I thought I told you
to get off my land.

47:57.750 --> 47:58.865
You know what, Maggie?

47:58.959 --> 48:03.123
You're not allowed to tell me
where I'm allowed to be.

48:03.506 --> 48:05.087
On my property, I am.

48:10.304 --> 48:12.215
I see you lost your backhoe.

48:14.016 --> 48:15.756
I see you lost your mind.

48:16.143 --> 48:18.930
And you're probably just gonna
leave it like this, aren't you?

48:19.438 --> 48:21.724
Just a big hole in the earth.

48:22.650 --> 48:23.935
Come back here,

48:24.485 --> 48:28.398
you dig a big, ugly, black hole,
then you take off again.

48:28.948 --> 48:30.154
That's what you do.

48:30.491 --> 48:31.480
You wish.

48:32.284 --> 48:34.525
I wish you'd leave me alone
is what I wish.

48:35.704 --> 48:39.162
I'm not gonna just
dig a hole here.

48:40.709 --> 48:43.576
I'm gonna build a house here.
I'm gonna live here.

48:43.838 --> 48:45.419
Not on my land you're not.

48:45.506 --> 48:49.169
(CHUCKLING) Why not?
What do you care? Hmm?

48:50.970 --> 48:54.554
You don't use it anyway.
Tom is dead and you're alone.

48:55.474 --> 48:57.339
You leave Tom out of this.

48:57.601 --> 49:00.263
You're alone, and he's not around
to protect you

49:00.354 --> 49:02.140
from your own misdeeds.

49:02.982 --> 49:04.563
(CHUCKLING) "Misdeeds."

49:05.109 --> 49:06.599
That's hilarious.

49:11.657 --> 49:12.737
You left.

49:13.993 --> 49:15.858
Oh, for the love of God.

49:17.204 --> 49:19.365
People leave and then they come back.

49:20.040 --> 49:22.201
Yeah, they come back
after their father's dead.

49:23.711 --> 49:25.451
He died calling your name.

49:25.546 --> 49:27.787
"Where's Maggie? Where's Maggie?"

49:27.882 --> 49:29.793
- Don't say that to me.
- "Where's my Maggie?"

49:29.884 --> 49:32.250
- Don't say that to me.
- Why not? It's true.

49:32.720 --> 49:35.678
You never told me how sick he was,
and that's on you,

49:36.056 --> 49:37.546
how you let him die.

49:38.517 --> 49:40.223
His room was a pigsty.

49:40.728 --> 49:42.719
There was garbage all over the floor.

49:42.813 --> 49:44.769
I was alone with a dying man.

49:45.649 --> 49:48.857
And you don't get to tell me
that I didn't do the dishes enough.

49:53.908 --> 49:54.988
You know what?

49:56.535 --> 49:58.742
When you're this close,
I can smell you.

50:00.247 --> 50:02.283
When was the last time
you took a bath?

50:04.084 --> 50:07.542
You smell like some
kind of dead animal in the woods.

50:09.965 --> 50:11.796
You don't like it, you can leave.

50:13.219 --> 50:15.084
Nobody wants you here anyway.

50:16.430 --> 50:17.419
It's my land.

50:18.641 --> 50:19.926
Not for long.

50:32.071 --> 50:33.857
(BOTH GRUNTING)

50:35.241 --> 50:36.356
YOUNG BEN: This is hard.

50:38.452 --> 50:39.441
(YOUNG BEN GRUNTS)

50:44.083 --> 50:46.870
So, we bury this and in 50 years,
we dig it up.

50:46.961 --> 50:47.950
It's a time capsule.

50:48.712 --> 50:50.248
But what if we forget where we put it?

50:50.339 --> 50:51.328
We won't forget.

50:51.549 --> 50:53.005
Gerry, do you have something
you want to put in?

50:53.968 --> 50:54.957
Here.

50:57.429 --> 50:59.215
- What's this?
- It's a heart.

50:59.765 --> 51:02.006
- YOUNG BEN: Can I put a heart in, too?
- Do you have one?

51:12.903 --> 51:14.564
Now, we bury it.

51:35.467 --> 51:36.456
(SIGHS)

51:59.575 --> 52:00.564
Hey.

52:01.285 --> 52:02.525
Hello, Gerry.

52:02.995 --> 52:04.201
Do you mind if I join you?

52:04.371 --> 52:05.702
Sure, come on up.

52:09.376 --> 52:12.459
- Two chairs set up all nice like this.
- (CHUCKLES)

52:13.172 --> 52:14.833
Looks like you were expecting me.

52:15.215 --> 52:16.455
That was Tom's chair.

52:16.550 --> 52:17.756
Oh, I'm sorry.

52:18.052 --> 52:19.633
That's... That's okay.

52:19.720 --> 52:21.256
He's been dead almost a year.

52:21.388 --> 52:23.504
Oh, I know. I just thought,

52:24.308 --> 52:28.142
well, maybe you didn't want
anybody sitting in his chair.

52:29.229 --> 52:33.097
Well, we used to sit out here
every night, you know,

52:33.192 --> 52:34.602
have a cocktail.

52:36.070 --> 52:38.903
Talk about the day, the weather.

52:39.073 --> 52:40.062
Hmm.

52:41.909 --> 52:43.740
One time, we saw a bear...

52:44.078 --> 52:45.238
(CHUCKLES)

52:45.913 --> 52:47.574
Come up to that tree.

52:47.665 --> 52:48.950
Mmm.

52:49.833 --> 52:50.822
A bear.

52:51.919 --> 52:53.204
That was something.

52:54.588 --> 52:55.919
Big black one.

52:57.925 --> 52:59.005
Oh. Um...

53:00.427 --> 53:01.587
These are for you.

53:12.439 --> 53:13.770
Yeah, I wanted to, uh...

53:15.275 --> 53:18.733
To come by and just say hi,
couple of times.

53:20.489 --> 53:22.229
But I didn't know...

53:25.119 --> 53:26.279
What didn't you know?

53:28.288 --> 53:30.153
You know, everybody was saying that

53:32.626 --> 53:37.120
you were missing Tom,
and I didn't want to intrude.

53:38.757 --> 53:39.746
(SIGHS)

53:39.842 --> 53:41.423
You want to come in, have a cocktail?

53:42.886 --> 53:45.093
- I do.
- Okay, come on.

53:50.060 --> 53:52.767
- You want a bourbon?
- Bourbon would be great.

53:58.944 --> 54:01.310
- Ice cube?
- lce cube. Sure.

54:03.532 --> 54:04.817
The place looks great.

54:08.662 --> 54:11.404
Ben came over and tromped
the whole thing to the ground.

54:11.498 --> 54:13.659
- What?
- You seen him lately?

54:14.626 --> 54:15.991
Couple of times, sure.

54:19.381 --> 54:21.497
- He just wants to come home.
- (CHUCKLES)

54:22.050 --> 54:23.506
He wants to steal home, you mean.

54:24.928 --> 54:26.884
Well, he's surely stealing things.

54:27.556 --> 54:29.763
Or actually, Curtis.

54:32.060 --> 54:34.267
They grabbed up your logging rights.

54:35.814 --> 54:37.850
It may not be such a bad idea.

54:38.484 --> 54:40.099
I mean, hejust wants
to do some logging,

54:40.194 --> 54:42.606
cut down a few trees.
It'll keep him out of trouble.

54:42.696 --> 54:44.027
(LAUGHS) Are you kidding?

54:44.281 --> 54:47.023
Ben doesn't wanna go back to work
cutting down trees.

54:47.618 --> 54:49.779
Now that he's got my logging rights,
he's going to...

54:50.287 --> 54:52.903
He's gonna grab the land
because of the taxes.

54:53.040 --> 54:54.120
- No.
- Yes.

54:54.208 --> 54:57.450
- Uh-uh.
- Yeah. Yeah. That's the plan.

54:58.462 --> 54:59.702
That's the whole thing.

55:00.589 --> 55:02.625
They're gonna steal my property,

55:02.716 --> 55:04.581
and then,
they're gonna kick me to the...

55:05.135 --> 55:06.124
Ah.

55:06.386 --> 55:08.502
And who knows even what they're
gonna do with me.

55:08.597 --> 55:12.010
They're probably gonna put me
in some nursing home with no windows,

55:12.100 --> 55:14.557
and terrible nurses
who tie you to the bed.

55:14.812 --> 55:15.801
- No.
- Yes.

55:15.896 --> 55:17.636
No, I'm sure
they're not gonna do that.

55:17.898 --> 55:18.887
Yes.

55:19.066 --> 55:20.727
And you know who's cooked this up?

55:20.818 --> 55:22.774
That kid he's running around with.

55:23.904 --> 55:25.769
Lord, that kid is the devil.

55:26.281 --> 55:27.396
Who is that kid anyway?

55:28.200 --> 55:29.485
You don't know who he is?

55:30.410 --> 55:31.650
No, who is he?

55:33.247 --> 55:34.737
He's Ben's son.

55:38.752 --> 55:41.414
- RAY: Rosa, Rosa Ramirez.
- (LAUGHING)

55:41.880 --> 55:43.461
Wicked and wild.

55:43.549 --> 55:45.414
- (COUGHING)
- (RAY LAUGHS)

55:46.218 --> 55:48.425
It was 1995, Rosa.

55:49.429 --> 55:51.340
She was the one, I'm telling you.

55:51.765 --> 55:53.096
The one that got away.

55:53.183 --> 55:54.844
BEN: Wait a minute, hey.

55:55.727 --> 55:57.058
Gerry, is that you?

55:57.437 --> 55:59.143
What's up, Gerry?
You got some groceries for us?

56:00.774 --> 56:03.356
BEN: What's this?
Oh, wait a minute. What...

56:04.528 --> 56:05.517
Great.

56:07.614 --> 56:08.854
You piece of shit.

56:09.241 --> 56:10.947
Gerry, you bring her here?

56:11.034 --> 56:12.023
GERRY: Yeah.

56:12.244 --> 56:14.200
You know, you guys,
she has a right to know.

56:14.830 --> 56:17.492
- You told her?
- He told me.

56:17.791 --> 56:20.783
He told me that this is your son.

56:21.295 --> 56:23.627
This shit-for-brains is my nephew.

56:24.715 --> 56:27.422
Wait, this is what
you're mad about now?

56:27.926 --> 56:31.214
I'm mad about so many different
things, you can't count that high.

56:32.139 --> 56:33.470
Get off my land.

56:34.141 --> 56:36.803
You get off my land.
You sold it to me.

56:37.519 --> 56:40.261
Get with the program.
You can't sell land.

56:40.647 --> 56:43.559
Yes, you can, because you did.

56:43.650 --> 56:45.015
No, you can't.

56:45.360 --> 56:46.896
- GERRY: Oh. Hey, hey.
- Oh, please.

56:47.195 --> 56:48.184
- What is this?
- GERRY: Calm down.

56:48.280 --> 56:50.817
- CURT: Hey, hey, hey.
- Yeah, or what?

56:50.908 --> 56:52.068
- RAY: Come on now, Ben.
- She can shoot at me

56:52.159 --> 56:53.444
but I can't shoot at her?

56:53.535 --> 56:56.117
- No, you can't. Put the gun down.
- I'm serious.

56:56.204 --> 56:57.193
Put...

56:57.831 --> 56:58.866
Whoa.

56:58.957 --> 57:00.538
- GERRY: Oh, Lord.
- Ben?

57:01.001 --> 57:03.413
- Oh, Lord.
- Ben, you okay?

57:03.503 --> 57:04.492
(BEN GROANING)

57:05.339 --> 57:06.749
Ben? Come here.

57:06.840 --> 57:08.421
What are you so worried about him?

57:08.508 --> 57:10.840
- Ben?
- I'm the one he shot at.

57:11.428 --> 57:13.760
- He's not breathing right.
- Talk to me, Ben.

57:13.847 --> 57:14.927
(BEN GROANING)

57:15.015 --> 57:16.926
RAY: Ben.
GERRY: Let's get you on your feet.

57:17.017 --> 57:18.006
RAY: Come on.

57:19.519 --> 57:21.680
You can't hold him that tight.
He can't breathe.

57:21.772 --> 57:23.433
You okay, Ben? Ben, you okay?

57:23.523 --> 57:24.808
Yes, he's okay. I got him.

57:24.900 --> 57:26.731
- Get out of the way.
- Whoa, whoa. Hey, hey.

57:26.818 --> 57:28.729
You get out of the way!
You're the one who shot him!

57:28.904 --> 57:30.314
MAGGIE: That was days ago.
CURT: So?

57:31.073 --> 57:33.189
So, he's been getting stoned
in the woods ever since.

57:33.283 --> 57:34.443
You think that's good for him?

57:34.534 --> 57:36.115
- We need a doctor!
- GERRY: We need a doctor!

57:36.203 --> 57:37.443
Look, marijuana's medicinal.

57:37.537 --> 57:38.526
You're an idiot.

57:39.498 --> 57:40.487
Not again.

57:40.916 --> 57:41.996
Somebody help me here.

57:42.084 --> 57:44.040
Oh, my God, it's... We need a gurney.

57:44.211 --> 57:46.042
Wasn't this guy, like, just here?

57:46.213 --> 57:48.044
Get a gurney, now.

57:48.382 --> 57:49.417
I'm back.

57:49.549 --> 57:50.538
I can see that. Stay still.

57:50.676 --> 57:52.462
- Did you see... Did you...
- RAY: He just fell down.

57:52.552 --> 57:53.632
- Ma'am...
- MAGGIE: Take his...

57:53.720 --> 57:56.336
- Get out of here.
- Against the wall, please. Thank you.

58:11.530 --> 58:12.519
Doctor.

58:17.327 --> 58:18.567
Maggie Farmer?

58:20.247 --> 58:21.236
That's me.

58:21.832 --> 58:23.242
Your brother is very sick.

58:24.084 --> 58:25.244
When he was shot,

58:25.711 --> 58:29.374
the bullet perforated the bottom lobe
of the left lung.

58:29.464 --> 58:31.045
It had really not
begun to heal properly

58:31.133 --> 58:32.293
when he checked himself out.

58:32.592 --> 58:34.253
It's been gathering fluid.

58:34.511 --> 58:37.674
He's developed pneumonia,
and the lung collapsed.

58:39.266 --> 58:42.053
We have him on a respirator,
but it's very bad.

58:45.564 --> 58:47.100
"Very bad." What does that mean?

58:49.526 --> 58:51.437
It's touch and go. I'm sorry.

58:55.449 --> 58:56.780
Can I see him?

58:57.701 --> 59:00.693
You're the one who shot him
Ms. Farmer, so, no.

59:01.204 --> 59:02.239
I'm not letting you up there.

59:03.290 --> 59:04.279
I'm his son.

59:04.624 --> 59:08.287
You can go in.
He's in intensive care, room 1422.

59:09.796 --> 59:12.037
Uh, I'm his friend. Can I go up?

59:12.132 --> 59:13.872
Yeah. Go.

59:23.435 --> 59:25.471
(MACHINES BEEPING)

01:01:45.952 --> 01:01:48.034
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

01:02:27.494 --> 01:02:30.827
"Snow White was more quiet
and gentle than Rose Red.

01:02:31.331 --> 01:02:35.040
"Rose Red liked better to run about
in the meadows and fields,

01:02:35.168 --> 01:02:37.625
"seeking flowers,
and catching butterflies.

01:02:38.797 --> 01:02:40.753
"But Snow White sat at home
with her mother,

01:02:40.840 --> 01:02:42.705
"and helped her with her housework,

01:02:43.134 --> 01:02:45.625
"or read to her
when there was nothing to do."

01:02:53.812 --> 01:02:55.552
I'm sorry I shot you.

01:03:00.026 --> 01:03:01.857
I'm sorry I shot you, Benny.

01:03:17.919 --> 01:03:19.375
I'm sorry.

01:03:23.133 --> 01:03:24.373
(EXHALES)

01:03:35.687 --> 01:03:36.676
Oh.

01:03:37.230 --> 01:03:38.219
Hello.

01:03:38.648 --> 01:03:39.637
You the lawyer?

01:03:40.400 --> 01:03:42.015
- Samuelson?
- Uh...

01:03:43.069 --> 01:03:44.900
I'm sor... I'm sorry, do I know you?

01:03:45.530 --> 01:03:47.111
I'm Ben Farmer's son.

01:03:47.615 --> 01:03:50.823
Oh, yes. Yes, I heard. That's...

01:03:51.911 --> 01:03:53.242
Come, come, come.

01:03:57.125 --> 01:03:58.114
How is Ben?

01:03:59.210 --> 01:04:00.199
He's bad.

01:04:01.004 --> 01:04:01.993
Oh.

01:04:02.213 --> 01:04:04.579
I heard he was doing better.
He's not still in the hospital?

01:04:05.467 --> 01:04:07.253
Very much still in the hospital.

01:04:08.303 --> 01:04:09.543
I think he's gonna die.

01:04:11.598 --> 01:04:13.964
I'm sorry to hear it.

01:04:14.768 --> 01:04:16.599
That doesn't do anybody any good.

01:04:18.438 --> 01:04:19.427
Well...

01:04:20.190 --> 01:04:21.521
My assistant's not in yet.

01:04:21.608 --> 01:04:24.190
I'd offer you coffee,
or condolences...

01:04:24.277 --> 01:04:26.518
Look, I got to say this, 'cause I
have to be on top of this now.

01:04:26.613 --> 01:04:28.820
If Ben dies,
it's because his sister shot him.

01:04:31.368 --> 01:04:32.699
So, what's the question?

01:04:33.703 --> 01:04:36.194
I'm his only living heir, right?

01:04:36.289 --> 01:04:38.826
I mean, she can't shoot him
and then inherit all that land.

01:04:38.917 --> 01:04:42.455
- That doesn't make any sense.
- Okay. Come. Uh, sit down.

01:04:47.008 --> 01:04:49.875
First things first.
Does Ben have a will?

01:04:51.221 --> 01:04:52.210
Does that matter?

01:04:52.597 --> 01:04:53.632
If he has a will, of course,

01:04:53.723 --> 01:04:55.839
his worldly possessions
will be distributed accordingly.

01:04:55.934 --> 01:04:58.550
If he doesn't have one,
everything goes to the next of kin.

01:04:58.645 --> 01:05:02.263
Okay. Right.
Is that me or his sister?

01:05:02.357 --> 01:05:04.222
Well, you were right a moment ago.

01:05:04.317 --> 01:05:07.184
If he dies from a gunshot wound
which she inflicted,

01:05:07.320 --> 01:05:09.402
the law nullifies her claim.

